fidius-core/src/package.rs.doc_comment:
Load and parse a `package.toml` manifest from a package directory.

The type parameter `M` is the host's metadata schema. If the `[metadata]`
section doesn't deserialize into `M`, this returns `PackageError::ParseError`.

# Example

```ignore
#[derive(Deserialize)]
struct MySchema {
category: String,
min_host_version: String,
}

let manifest = load_manifest::<MySchema>(Path::new("./my-package/"))?;
println!("Package: {} v{}", manifest.package.name, manifest.package.version);
println!("Category: {}", manifest.metadata.category);
```

fidius-macro/src/lib.rs.doc_comment:
Define a plugin interface from a trait.

Generates a `#[repr(C)]` vtable struct, interface hash constant,
capability bit constants, and a descriptor builder function.

# Example

```ignore
#[plugin_interface(version = 1, buffer = PluginAllocated)]
pub trait Greeter: Send + Sync {
fn greet(&self, name: String) -> String;

#[optional(since = 2)]
fn greet_fancy(&self, name: String) -> String;
}
```

Implement a plugin interface for a concrete type.

Generates extern "C" FFI shims, a static vtable, a plugin descriptor,
and a plugin registry.

# Example

```ignore
pub struct MyGreeter;

#[plugin_impl(Greeter)]
impl Greeter for MyGreeter {
fn greet(&self, name: String) -> String {
format!("Hello, {name}!")
}
}
```
